wikipedia_page.main: Sylvia Law OBE (29 March 1931 – 1 April 2004) was a British town planner who was the first woman to be elected as President of the Royal Town Planning Institute.

response: A full list of Presidents is set out below. The first President, in 1914, was Thomas Adams. The first female President, in 1974, was Sylvia Law.
